{
  "stem": "8569.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she was telling me that there was no order, that they are going-- that everything is going to be OK.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she wouldn't tell me the truth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "On the day of the execution, I was in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And Marta came to take me out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The union commander was released earlier to witness the execution.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But Marta's friends, [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH], grabbed me and put me in the block, so that I wouldn't have to witness it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I didn't know what was going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I suspected, but I wasn't sure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when we were on the block and I wanted to run out, they bodily held me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They wouldn't let me out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I heard this collective groan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I knew what happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So I wasn't-- I didn't witness it with my eyes, but I was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, I don't remember it by heart.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I have it written, her last letter that I got through Marta, in which she is saying [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] that all hope is gone, that through her window of the cell, she can see the feet of the prisoners that are coming back from work, that all the hated sounds of the camp life-- the screaming for the soup and for the tea that was so hateful to her-- were so dear to her now, that all hope is gone, and that she so much wants to live.",
      "word_count": 91
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I lost my mind immediately after that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The execution was on January 5th.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The evacuation of Auschwitz was on January 18, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Five.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The Russians liberated Auschwitz on January 19-27, but the Germans evacuated Auschwitz on January 18, when we went on the death march.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't want to move from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
